Introduction

The data set I chose was the Top 500 albums ranked by Rolling Stone in 2020 This list is interesting because it highlights albums that have made a significant impact in music history. The data includes various details like the year the album was released, its genre, the type of album (like studio or live), how well it did on the Billboard charts, and its popularity on Spotify. The information was gathered Rolling Stone, where they critiqued each album and ranked it on their specific scale. One source that analyzes this concept of What makes an album great is linked here. My outcome variable is Spotify Popularity and my predictors are weeks on billboard, peak billboard position, and the genre of the album.

Bivariate Relationship

3. Bivariate Relationship

The correlation coefficient between the weeks on billboard and the spotify popularity of albums is 0.3736067.There is a positive weak correlation, it is .3736067. This means that the increase in weeks on the billboard means there is a slight increase to the spotify popularity but not marginal at all. The correlation coefficient between the peak billboards and the spotify popularity of albums is -0.4333722. There is a negative weak correlation, it is -.4333722 which means that it is moving in slightly opposite directions. This means that as the peak billboard position of an album increases, the spotify popularity of the album slightly decreases but not marginally at all. Overall both correlations are very weak.

Conclusion

This analysis of the Top 500 albums by Rolling Stone shows a weak negative correlation between Billboard performance and Spotify popularity. Specifically, weeks on the Billboard chart (r = 0.37) and peak Billboard position (r = -0.43) do not strongly predict Spotify success. The average spotify popularity was 57.78, this shows that there is a varied popularity and overall reception among albums. This shows that researches should look at factors like marketing strategies or social media strategies, such as tiktok to understand what makes an album popular in terms of streaming.
